definition: Bulgaria/Bulgarian/abbr. for 保加利亞|保加利亚[Bao3 jia1 li4 ya4]
to defend/to protect/to keep/to guarantee/to ensure/civil administration unit in the baojia 保甲[bao3 jia3] system (old)

sentences.english: Safe boxes, fancy clock, mini fans, timers.
sentences.chinese: 保險盒，玩具鍾，微型風扇，記時器。

sentences.english: Purloined the key to his safe - deposit box.
sentences.chinese: 拿走了他保險盒的鑰匙。

sentences.english: Take fuse box cover off on right side and take out the lower screw going into the lower dash.
sentences.chinese: 取下右側的保險盒蓋子，取出較低儀表板上的螺絲。

sentences.english: Specially provide car audio electronic accessories kit, such as fuse, FM/ power convertor.
sentences.chinese: 汽車功放電子零配件，保險絲，保險盒等。

sentences.english: The fuse box can prevent that small problems become big problems.
sentences.chinese: 保險盒防止小問題變成大問題。

sentences.english: I've blown the fuse in the fuse box over and over again.
sentences.chinese: 我把保險盒裏的保險絲一再熔斷。
